  "prompt": "Do questions on Quora that are non-anonymous get more distribution when posted as a follow-up to another question?",
  "response": "While there isn't official data from Quora specifically stating that non-anonymous questions receive more distribution when posted as follow-ups, there are a few factors that could influence their visibility:\n\n1. **Contextual Relevance**: Follow-up questions can benefit from the context established by the original question. This relevance may encourage users to engage with the follow-up.\n\n2. **Engagement**: If the original question is popular and attracts a lot of answers and interactions, a follow-up might gain more visibility due to the ongoing activity on the thread.\n\n3. **Notifications**: Users following the original question might receive notifications about the follow-up, increasing its exposure.\n\n4. **Non-Anonymous Advantage**: Non-anonymous questions tend to foster community engagement, as users can see who is asking and may be more inclined to respond.\n\nThat said, distribution can also depend on how well the follow-up question is framed, the timing of the post, and the interests of the Quora user base. Overall, while there could be a potential advantage to posting non-anonymous follow-up questions, individual experiences may vary.",
